Raila Odinga (AFP) Multimedia &nbsp; &nbsp; User Galleries &nbsp; &nbsp; News in Pictures Send us your pictures &nbsp; &nbsp; Send us your stories Nairobi - Veteran political leader and former prime minister Raila Odinga was on Thursday named Kenya's opposition presidential candidate for August's elections, at a large rally in the capital Nairobi.The public announcement was made by senior leaders of the National Super Alliance (NASA) coalition of which Odinga will be flag bearer, challenging President Uhuru Kenyatta in a repeat of the 2013 election line-up.24.com encourages commentary submitted via MyNews24. Contributions of 200 words or more will be considered for publication.